t with a f=\r\norm *they create* based on one of the archetypal forms and eventually one d=\r\nay this self-created form merges into the Universal form of the Devata.=C2=\r\n=A0\n\n&lt;&lt;=E2=80=9CAham Brahmam asmi=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Ctat twam asi=E2=80=\r\n=9D are the two famous sayings from the Vedas.&gt;&gt;\n\nThese two are great mahav=\r\nakya and very relevant. But IMHO they become complete when taken with the t=\r\nhird Mahavakya - which is unfortunately often ignored in practice - Sarvam =\r\nKhalvidam Brahman (*everything* is Brahman).=C2=A0\n\nIt is absolutely true t=\r\nhat one need not worship a Devata for self-realization, (a Devata can very =\r\nwell take one to self-realization or atmagyan or whatever term one likes). =\r\n=C2=A0That is not my contention in this write-up. But the inferences or des=\r\ncriptions are not totally complete or correct in every aspect IMO.\n\nThe Suf=\r\nis, almost every single one of them, eventually start focusing on the Divin=\r\ne Light the see. Technically that is a form too - anything that vibrates an=\r\nd is perceivable, within or without, has a form. They do not worship the De=\r\nvatas we Hindus worship, which is perfectly fine. But that does not mean th=\r\nat the Devatas have no independent existence of their own or are a creation=\r\n of a human mind! :)\n\nJust exploring the edges of this write-up!\n\n-Regards\n=\r\n=C2=A0Rajarshi\n\n\n\n\nI have a hundred lives before me yet/ To grasp thee in, =\r\nO spirit ethereal, / Be sure I will with heart insatiate/ Pursue thee like =\r\na hunter through them all.-Sri Aurobindo\n\n\n\nOn Tuesday, 7 January 2014 3:31=\r\n PM, &quot;aks_day@...&quot; &lt;aks_day@...&gt; wrote:\n \n=C2=A0 \nHi Rajarshi, =\r\n\n\n\nPlease read next few paras where he has explained the manifestation of i=\r\nshta as a necessary step to reach final goal.\n\n\n\r\n---2020808392-79639157-1389091510=:96503\r\nContent-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printabl